This guide provides a step-by-step procedure for adding two additional virtual drives to a virtual machine (VM). It covers different hypervisor platforms like VMware vSphere, Microsoft Hyper-V, and Oracle VirtualBox. After completing the procedure, you will also learn how to verify the addition of the new drives within the guest operating system.
** Steps for Adding Two Virtual Drives to a VM**

- Power Off the Virtual Machine (if necessary)

- : Access the VM Settings

- Add the First Virtual Drive.

